  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The soldiers beat the protestors night after night",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The police and soldiers suddenly entered the old parliament complex armed with weapons and launched indiscriminate attacks on the protesters who were engaged in satyagraha protest in the presidential complex.",
        "At a time when no one expected, the action attack, which was launched by the soldiers after midnight on July 22, was carried out until 3 am yesterday (22). As a result, the area looked like a huge wasteland.",
        "Soldiers also launched a barrage of attacks on local and foreign journalists who rushed to the spot after hearing about the incident. They even tried to break some people's cameras.",
        "Despite the pleas of 'Leave us, we are leaving', the soldiers carried out indiscriminate attacks, stamping on the backs, arms and legs of the women protestors without even looking at them. They also caused injuries.",
        "The protestors had given a written assurance to the Fort police on July 21st that they would leave the place yesterday (22nd) around noon and had also handed over a letter.",
        "However, the police, special operations forces, and air force entered Nadunisi and launched indiscriminate attacks on the protestors who were carrying out satyagraha.",
        "Opposition politicians, civil society organizations and international diplomats have strongly condemned these attacks as 'friendly attacks'.",
        "It is learned that after the attack, the soldiers who brought the area under their control, placed barriers so that the people there could not go out and conducted strict investigations.",
        "Protesters claim that many people have been taken away by the soldiers and that they do not know what happened to them.",
        "However, the Police Media Unit, which stated that nine protesters have been arrested, issued a media statement yesterday (22) morning saying that steps have been taken to present them in court.",
        "The soldiers there even prevented those injured from the attacks in Nadunisi from being taken to the hospital. However, the protesters said that only a few people were admitted to the hospital.",
        "Hearing about the incident, many people stormed towards the President's Secretariat through various routes. However, iron fences were erected to prevent entry from any side and a large number of security forces were deployed on security duty.",
        "Earlier there were reports that attacks were carried out on 'Kota Ko Kama'. However, no damage was done to the Kama. In addition, lawyers also rushed to the place yesterday morning to inquire about the police station where the arrested protestors were detained.",
        "However, the police there did not give any answer to the questions of the lawyers. In this case, yesterday (22) a protest was held in front of Colombo Fort railway station to condemn the indiscriminate attack carried out by the soldiers."
      ],
